<p>After graduating from Oberlin in 2010, I moved to Boston to be with Jessie while she finished her degree at Olin. When Jessie entered her senior year, I realized we had been together for nearly eight years, and I decided the time was right. During that fall, I planned the perfect proposal. We flew to San Diego for the winter holidays, and on December 23, ring secretly in hand, I suggested we watch the sunset from our favorite spot: the cliffs in Torrey Pines. Just after sunset, I got down on one knee and asked her to marry me, and, of course, she said “yes!”</p></td>
